.TH VAF-REGISTER 8 "2026-06-10" "versatile-autoreg-vaf" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
vaf-register \- one-shot VAF registration in the upper VAS
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B vaf-register
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B vaf-register
performs a single registration cycle: it downloads the local VAS inventory
and registers it in the upper VAS as
.BR extra_imperative.VAF_<KEY> ,
then exits.
.PP
It is called by the
.B local-vaf-register
hook installed in
.I /etc/vas/hooks.d/
by the
.BR vaf (8)
package postinst. The hook fires on every
.B bump_version()
event in the local VAS, providing sub-second propagation of inventory
changes to the upper VAS without waiting for the
.BR vaf (8)
daemon's next CHECK cycle.
.PP
.B vaf-register
reads the same configuration as
.BR vaf (8)
from
.I /etc/vaf/vaf.conf
and
.IR /etc/vaf/vaf.conf.d/ .
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR vaf (8),
.BR vas (8)
